<dl id="n09018d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09018d">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09018d"> 18(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Poincar&eacute; change &mdash; / clicks / span discrete points</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">If the quantum hypothesis is generally adopted even more radical alterations in our thinking will be necessary. But I feel it premature even to suggest their direction in the present unsatisfactory state of quantum mechanics. It may be that as <mark>Poincare</mark> (the other Poincare) suggested we shall be forced to conceive of <mark>all changes as occurring in a series of clicks, and all space as consisting of discrete points</mark>. <small> J. B. S. Haldane, <a name="DAED" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DAED"><cite title="source">Dedalus</cite></a> (1923) 17f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
